Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
ref: Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Data For Sci.and Technol.,Mito 1988, p.691 (1988)
title: -Optical Model Analysis Over A Wide Range of Nuclei Using Polarized Neutron Scattering Data.

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Data For Sci.and Technol.,Mito 1988, p.691 (1988)

x4freetext: -OPTICAL MODEL ANALYSIS OVER A WIDE RANGE OF NUCLEI
STUTTGART SCORPION FACILITY. THE 4 MEV DYNAMI-
TRON DELIVERED 500 MICROAMPS OF ALPHA-PARTICLES ONTO
FOUR NE 213 LIQUID SCINTILLATION DETECTORS AND
FOUR MONITORS WERE LOCATED TOGETHER WITH THE NEUTRON-
PRODUCTION TARGET AND A SPIN-FLIP MAGNET IN A CLOSE
DOUBLY-SHIELDED GEOMETRY. THE CONTRIBUTION OF GAMMA-
RAYS WAS KEPT BELOW 1 PERCENT BY MEANS OF N-GAMMA
DISCRIMINATION. THE RESOLUTION OF THE NEUTRON DETEC-
.DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR FLUX ATTENUATION, MULTIPLE
SCATTERING AND DEPOLARIZATION IN THE SAMPLES.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: ANALYZING POWERS ARE GIVEN WITH THE STATISTICAL ERRORS
ONLY. TO THIS SHOULD BE ADDED THE SCALE UNCERTAINTY,
WHICH IS ESTIMATED TO BE 10 PERCENT.
